@tysonnorris I have now modified the query to check if key is also defined. So now the where clause looks like

```SELECT r AS view FROM root r JOIN n in r.namespaces WHERE (NOT(IS_DEFINED(r.blocked)) OR r.blocked = false) AND ((r.subject = @name AND IS_DEFINED(r.key)) OR n.name = @name)```

This ensures if no key is defined at top level then it would not lead to duplicate results

